title: Grateful Dead Live at Santa Cruz County Fairgrounds on 1983-09-24
description: Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, They Love Each Other, Me & My Uncle, Mexicali Blues, Bird Song, Hell In A Bucket, Deep Elem Blues-> Looks Like Rain-> Day Job China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Women Are Smarter, Ship of Fools, Truckin'-> Drums-> Uncle John's Band-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away-> Brokedown Palace, E: Finiculi Finicula, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text:
GD Picinic This was a sunny day in Santa Cruz mountains. This had a big family picnic feel to it. My first show (of many).
 
I don't know if it was the roses, but the sky was yellow and the sun was blue. The highlights of the show were Birdsong, Uncle John's Band and Brokedown Palace.

strong show this one sounds very good.

The Deep Ellum is so Funky, and Brokedown is on the all time list. 

------
the other source has a sbd first set, and this wonderful source for the second set.

Great Show It was a sunny day, they played in a baseball field if I remember. I had just seen them in Ventura, and this was a wonderful show, prehaps even stronger.  I brought a friend of mine and he was more impressed with Bobby than Jerry. Bobby played very well that day.  Cd quality is great. This is one you want.

bad recording i think some of these reviewers are still at the show....i just downloaded the first song and i have to say it sounds like a 10 year old cassette that has been sitting in the hot sun....pretty much terrible quality...wouldn't bother with it
First California Show This was my 1st CA show after being on the East Coast and after 2 years in Japan - Thought it was awesome. Drove from San Diego and was not disappointed.

Best Audience sound on this site The second set was on my wish list since hearing the first almost twenty years ago.  The sound is in your ear!  A funky danceable China>Rider and an intense Truckin' make this essential dead

smokin! Just came back from watching dirt track racing at Santa Cruz County Fairgrounds(aka Watsonville Speedway)and put this on when I got home and the magic began!!This is a special show all the way through played in a magical place...Please Enjoy

P.S.the high treble mellows out a bit after the Alabama or you just get used to it I guess-either way this show is a true gem:-))
To aud, or not to aud. I have to say I typically hate audience tapes.  However, this audience version is so clean that it's the closest soundboard quality I've heard yet.  5 stars for sound quality.
Crispy AUD I have the SBD of the first set, but for the second set, this IS the AUD, nice recording! Ship of Fools almost feels like a SBD! Sweet!

fantastic show and sound top rate fob sound that improves early in first set; wasnt wowed by look of 2nd set -- but an exceedingly brilliant quality to the playing, energy and creativity the entire set 2. china cat>rider, truckin and ujb rule; brokedown show closer adds to unique element of show.
What a Day! I had so much fun at this show it wasn't legal.  Beautiful place, small crowd and great show.  Thanks for posting it.

Thirty-Nine Years Ago Today? Wow.  Time is passing quickly now in my  late-50s.  Me and a buddy somehow made it to this one-off, ate some Sluggo blotter, and had an epic time.  My memory ain't so clear on this one, but we somehow got back to Santa Cruz where there was a classic car show going on, and we just waltzed around shit-grin happy, and finally crashed under the cover of a catamaran.  Oh to be young and attuned to the GD Circus.  Thanks, Jerry!

PS:  I believe this is the last electric Deep Elem???
